The paper deals with sparsification of graphs, which is a topic in both theoretical computer science and applied mathematics. The focus is on planar graphs, which suggests categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.NA (numerical analysis). The paper also involves optimization and approximation, which could fall under cs.GT (game theory and economics) or cs.SI (social and information networks).
